empirical /ɛmˈpɪrɪkəl/

1. ADJ Empirical evidence or study relies on practical experience rather than theories. 实证的 

例： There is no empirical evidence to support his thesis. 没有实证根据来支持他的论点。 

2. empirically ADV 实证地 

例： They approached this part of their task empirically. 他们实证地处理这部分任务。

